snippet: The Republican-led bill is ultimately expected to pass both chambers, but faces certain veto by President Obama.
abstract: Senate votes, 52 to 47, to approve legislation that would appeal Affordable Care Act; measure would also end federal funding of Planned Parenthood, and is expected to pass House as well, but will likely be vetoed by Pres Obama.
lead_paragraph: The Republican-led bill is ultimately expected to pass both chambers, but faces certain veto by President Obama.
